ğŸ”„ Complete Test Flow Example
python# The tests now follow this realistic flow:
1. Create Hub        â†’ POST /hubs/ {"hub_id": 1, "solar_capacity_kw": 1000}
2. Create Battery    â†’ POST /batteries/ {"battery_id": 1, "hub_id": 1}
3. Create User       â†’ POST /users/ {"user_id": 1, "hub_id": 1}
4. Login User        â†’ POST /auth/token {"username": "admin", "password": "admin123"}
5. Post Live Data    â†’ POST /webhook/live-data {battery sensor data}
6. Verify Storage    â†’ Check database contains the data
7. Update Hub        â†’ PUT /hubs/1 {"solar_capacity_kw": 2000}
8. Update Battery    â†’ PUT /batteries/1 {"status": "maintenance"}
9. Delete Battery    â†’ DELETE /batteries/1
